newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia rubber ends little changed.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia rubber ends little changed.

text.p: Malaysian rubber prices ended little changed in another thin trading session with buyers keeping at the sidelines waiting for attractive levels.
Dealers said the market only saw selective latex inquiries from European and local glove and condom manufacturers.
"They (latex buyers) are still looking for lower levels," a dealer at a trading firm said. Drum latex prices are currently quoted at around 238 to 240 cents.
Buying interest from the Far East also remained thin with Chinese consumers checking market prices. Only routine hand-to-mouth business was reported.
December RSS One buyer ended 1.50 cents up at 321 cents ($1.27) a kg and December SMR 20 buyer was unchanged at 311.
Dealers said that the market expected a tight supply because of rains in some main growing areas in Malaysia.
The INRO five-day average was 244.26 Malaysian/Singapore cents per kg on November 19 from 244.45 on November 18. The daily indicator was 244.62 against 244.34.
